General Notes are in their original location at the end of the play,
followed by the text-critical notes originally printed at the bottom of
each page. All notes are hyperlinked in both directions. In dialogue,
a link from a speaker’s name generally means that the note applies
to the entire line or group of lines.

Line numbers—shown in the right margin and used for all
notes—are from the original text. In prose passages the exact line
counts will depend on your browser settings, and will probably be
different from the displayed numbers. Stage directions were not included
in the line numbering.
